## Actions
1. Replace any "survives a density-conditioned null" phrasing in A.5 with a
   descriptive-consistency claim. Proposed sentence (author to approve):

   "The pre-2007 co-citation network does separate into communities that
   align by name with the three traditions, and that partition's cohesion
   far exceeds a degree-preserving configuration-model null (within-
   tradition share 0.89 vs 0.37, z ≈ 25, N = 1000). The partition is
   optimised on the same graph, however, so it corroborates the reading
   only weakly; a labelling fixed a priori from the traditions' anchor
   works cannot sharpen it, because outside environmental economics those
   works fall below the co-citation core of this thin pre-2007 slice. We
   therefore read the separation as consistent with the citation structure,
   not independently confirmed by it."

2. Do NOT claim non-circular confirmation, "two independent statistics", or
   "~26 sd survival". One statistic, honestly; the null figure belongs to
   the fitted (circular) partition and must be labelled as such.
3. Cite the numbers by provenance (regenerable Make target + config seed).
4. Keep the HET register; state what the test shows and what it cannot.

